qas.question: In May 2012, who started the parliamentary elections?
What led to the loss of power of traditional Greek parties?

answers.text: their support on the politics of Mnimonio and the austerity measures

qas.question: Who became the second major party after the elections?

qas.question: What was the demographic result of the second election?

answers.text: coalition government composed of New Democracy (29%), PASOK (12%) and Democratic Left (6%) parties.

context: <a0_0>The coalition government<a0_0/> led the country to the parliamentary elections of May 2012. The power of the traditional Greek political parties, PASOK and New Democracy, declined from 43% to 13% and from 33% to 18%, respectively, due to <a1_0>their support on the politics of Mnimonio and the austerity measures<a1_0/>. <a2_0>The leftist party of SYRIZA<a2_0/> became the second major party, with an increase from 4% to 16%. <a3_0>No party could form a sustainable government<a3_0/>, which led to the parliamentary elections of June 2012. The result of the second elections was the formation of a <a4_0>coalition government composed of New Democracy (29%), PASOK (12%) and Democratic Left (6%) parties.
